]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The DT lifecycle is represented through MBSE modeling layers: a requirements stage where functional needs are captured; a functional architecture stage describing functions and interfaces; a logical architecture stage defining component‑connector structures using ADLs (e.g., ACME, AADL, MontiArc) and SysML Internal Block Diagrams; and a product/technical stage that links the logical model to concrete implementation artifacts such as Simulink models or C++/Java code. Transitions between stages are managed by traceability links defined in the SysML model, and governance is provided by the MBSE process that ensures each model artifact is reviewed at its respective stage."
]
